speakers.title: Intel Fellow
speakers.bio: Dr. Debendra Das Sharma is a recognized industry expert in IO subsystem and interconnect architectures. He is responsible for delivering Intel-wide critical interconnect technologies in Peripheral Component Interconnect Express (PCI Express), Compute Express Link, Coherency interconnects, Multi-Chip Package interconnect, and Rack Scale Architecture. He leads the path-finding, architectural specification, design and external ecosystem enabling of these I/O technologies. Debendra has been leading the development of PCI Express since its inception two decades back through six generations of evolution of the technology. He has played a key role in evolving PCI Express as the ubiquitous I/O interconnect in the industry, spanning the entire compute continuum. Debendra is a highly respected member of the Board of Directors for the PCI Special Interest Group.
